<paragraph blockId="18.[151,547,332,391]" box="[151,302,366,391]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,252,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 13 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[257,1354,196,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[237,1354,193,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 13 – 24. Habitus: 13, Philonthus quadraticeps Boheman; 14, P. discoideus (Gravenhorst); 15, P. bicoloristylus Chani- Posse; 16, P. bruchianus Chani-Posse; 17, P. flavolimbatus Erichson; 18, P. bonariensis Bernhauer; 19, P. longicornis Stephens; 20, P. argus Herman; 21, Styngetus viduus (Erichson); 22, Xenopygus analis (Erichson); 23, Nordus elytisi Chatzimanolis; 24, Oligotergus ogloblini Bernhauer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229559/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[264,293,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 42 – 49" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,509,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,509,1655]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 42 – 49. Abdomen: 42, Platydracus scabrosus; 43, Anotylus sp. Front tarsus: 44, Belonuchus rufipennis; 45, Philonthus longicornis; 46, Xenopygus analis; 47, Styngetus viduus. Femur: 48, Xenopygus analis; 49, Styngetus viduus. Abbreviation: Fe, femur." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229563/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">45</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,438,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Chani-Posse" box="[389,605,438,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Chani-Posse, M. (2010) Revision of the southern South American species of Philonthus Stephens (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 2595, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="2010">
Chani-Posse, 
<number box="[544,605,439,463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[623,879,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[623,879,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be identified by the eyes about as long as to slightly longer than temples, the antennal segment 
<number box="[720,734,475,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2.0">2</number>
shorter than preceding segment and antennal segments 
<number box="[1358,1436,475,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4 to 10</number>
elongate, the dorsal rows of pronotum each with five punctures and the paramere shifted toward right margin of median lobe. Length 
<number box="[389,423,546,571]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="6.5">6.5</number>
–7.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,582,607]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[364,625,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[364,625,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently considered a cosmopolitan species widely distributed in Central and South 
<collectingCountry box="[360,456,618,643]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Herman" box="[471,630,619,643]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalog of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millennium. Part V. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 265, 2441 - 3020." type="journal article" year="2001">
Herman 
<number box="[570,630,619,643]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,654,679]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Bionomics.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[342,603,654,678]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[342,603,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Philonthus longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been frequently found in cattle manure in open pastures of North 
<collectingCountry box="[151,247,690,715]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hu" box="[263,468,690,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Hu, G. Y. &amp; Frank, J. H. (1997) Predation on the horn fly (Diptera: Muscidae) by five species of Philonthus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Environmental Entomology, 26, 1240 - 1246." type="journal article" year="1997">
Hu &amp; Frank 
<number box="[411,468,691,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[533,645,690,715]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chani-Posse" box="[661,871,690,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Chani-Posse, M. R. (2004) Eight Argentinean species of dung-inhabiting Philonthus Stephens (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment, 39, 217 - 232. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650520412331271738" type="journal article" year="2004">
Chani-Posse 
<number box="[811,871,691,715]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and also cited from other organic debris such as decaying plants, other animal droppings, carcasses, etc (
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana" box="[788,955,726,751]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Smetana, A. (1995) Rove beetles of the subtribe Philonthina of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae): Classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 3, 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1995">
Smetana 
<number box="[895,955,726,751]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was also collected from pig carcasses in arid environment of 
<collectingCountry box="[520,631,762,787]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Aballay" box="[646,865,762,787]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" refString="Aballay, F. H., Murua, A. F., Acosta, J. C. &amp; Centeno, N. (2008) Primer registro de artropodofauna cadaverica en sustratos humanos y animales en San Juan, Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 67, 157 - 163." type="journal article" year="2008">
Aballay 
<emphasis box="[743,793,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 2012).
</paragraph>
